Definitions:
Globular Cluster : "Globular clusters are stable, tightly bound clusters of tens of thousands to millions of stars. They are associated with all types of galaxies."
  - Spherical shape due to intense gravity
  - "They are populated by older, redder stars than open clusters"
  - "within the Milky Way they are found in the halo and the bulge"







